---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<div class="tui-window blue-168 tui-page-window">
		<fieldset class="tui-fieldset white-255-border">
			<legend class="white-255-text">Frontend</legend>
			<p class="white-255-text">
				<a href="/" class="cyan-255-text">&larr; Back to Home</a>
			</p>
			<h1 class="white-255-text">Frontend</h1>
			<p class="white-255-text">
				Frontend development has undergone tremendous evolution since I embarked on my career. In the
				early days, being a frontend developer primarily meant working with HTML, CSS, and a sprinkle
				of JavaScript. Today, it encompasses a rich array of technologies and tools, many of which
				blur the lines with backend development. For instance, Node.js, originally just a JavaScript
				runtime, has become a powerful tool for building backend applications.
			</p>
			<p class="white-255-text">
				Despite these changes, my passion for frontend development remains unwavering. While my skills
				have expanded and I am now recognized as a full stack developer, my heart is still rooted in
				the frontend. I take pride in my ability to create seamless user experiences, but I also
				embrace the full stack landscape, allowing me to build comprehensive applications that thrive
				on both ends.
			</p>
		</fieldset>
	</div>
</Layout>
